      "content": "Zoning regulations in Portland, especially for RE-15, can be quite specific regarding commercial uses. Generally, RE-15 is primarily residential, meaning that establishing a retail use like a small grocery store would likely require a specific exception or be permitted under a limited mixed-use allowance. You should consult the official City of Portland zoning code or speak with a planning department representative to confirm the precise allowable uses for your specific corner lot. They will have the definitive answer on whether a small grocery store fits the designation.",
